AGI - Harry>, the rebel son of King Charles III>, will not be able to see his father in his 'two days' in London. The news is given by the British newspaper Daily Telegraph, according to which Duke of Sussex will not meet his father because of the dense calendar of the monarch. Prince Harry arrived in London this morning with a flight from the United States, where he lives with his wife Meghan and their two young children, Archie, who yesterday turned 5 years, and Lilibet. And he hoped that he could see the monarch, who is currently being treated for cancer?
&nbsp;
"In response to the numerous questions and continuous speculation about whether the Duke will meet or not with his father while he is in the UK this week, unfortunately this will not be possible because of the dense program of His Majesty," said a spokesman of Harry. The source adds that "the Duke obviously fully understands the program of commitments (of the king) and the other various priorities and hopes to meet him soon".
&nbsp;
Harry, who had no mystery of wanting to meet his father, is in London to participate in the meetings related to the Invictus Games >, the Games reserved for veterans of war wounded in combat. Tomorrow he is expected to a Thanksgiving event to celebrate the tenth anniversary of the Games at St Paul Cathedral in London, where he will hold a reading. For his part, according to Buckingham Palace, the king has a "intensive" program that will leave little room for any meetings with his younger son; just tomorrow, after the weekly meeting with Premier Rishi Sunak>, he will attend the first summer reception offered by Buckingham Palace for the season, in the gardens of the royal palace a few hundred meters from the place where Harry will be. Thursday has a public commitment outside London; and it is also continuing its treatment against cancer, which provide regular appointments in the hospital.
&nbsp;
The prince met his father last February at Clarence House, the residence where the monarch spent the night when he was in London and belonged to his grandmother, the mother queen. Once the news of his father's tumor was made, in February, Harry leaked that he would be willing to resume any of his public commitments, representing the Royal House, but the proposal was kindly declined by the palace. Thursday, Harry will fly to Nigeria where he will join his wife, Meghan, on a journey focused on the Games.&nbsp;

