AGI -&nbsp;Today schools and Slovak institutions, including banks, received over 1,100 bomb threats, causing evacuations across the country, said the police announcing the start of a terrorist investigation >.<br> "The act is investigated as a particularly serious crime of terrorist attack," said Rastislav Polakovic, Deputy Chief of Police.
&nbsp;
"The e-mails started arriving at schools today, from 5 to 6 in the morning," explained Rastislav Polakovic, the deputy chief of police, underlining that it is a "particularly serious crime of terrorist attack".<br> On his official Facebook page, the police said that he is "working at full pace, controlling security in schools and trying to identify" the authors of this "gas attack", which could risk. Lucia Forman, spokesman of the authorities of the capital Bratislava, said that she only registered threats of bombs in dozens of schools. "We took all the necessary measures, the children were evacuated and the police are dealing with the matter," he said.

