&nbsp;
He was sentenced for "incitement to commit murders >e for insulting religious holiness" > . Lawyer Babak Farsani stated that Mehrabi was found guilty of the capital crime of "corruption on the ground" > recalling that he can still appeal against the judgment at the Supreme Court > The protests, lasted months and unleashed by the death of Amini, have seen hundreds of deaths in the square clashes, including dozens of security agents. Thousands of people have been arrested to sedate those that authorities have defined "returns" instigated from abroad.
&nbsp;
Last month, an Iranian court sentenced the popular rapper Toomaj Salehi to death for supporting demonstrations. Nine executions have already been carried out on men deemed guilty of crimes related to protests, in particular violence against security forces. According to Amnesty International, in 2023 Iran performed death sentences of 853 people, the highest number since 2015.&nbsp;

